Array Properties in Java
1. âœ… Fixed Size
Once an array is created, its size cannot be changed.

2. âœ… Indexed Access
Array elements are accessed using indexes starting from 0.

3. âœ… Same Data Type
All elements in the array must be of the same type.

4. âœ… Stored in Contiguous Memory
Arrays are stored in continuous memory locations, so they allow fast access.

