ğŸ§¾ âœ… What is an Array Literal?
An array literal lets you create an array and assign values directly at the same time, without using new keyword and without specifying size.


âœ… Syntax:
int[] numbers = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};

here:
int[] â†’ array of integers
{10, 20, 30, 40, 50} â†’ array literal


in simple language:
Jab hum array banate waqt hi usme values daal dete hain, usse Array Literal kehte hain.
